caption: I absolutely love this BBQ restaurant they are so amazing and friendly. The food is absolutely delicious and tender and so very juicy. I have never had anything dry from them.
Food was very bland. The meat fall off the bones but salt and pepper could not help the lack of favor and taste.
I wouldn't say this is the best barbecue in Georgia but it definitely tops my top ten list. Their Brunswick stew and Red beans and rice are spot on DELICIOUS. I will be coming back.
Esta muy rica la comida y el sitio es muy agradable. Buen BBQ.
Absolutely amazing food.  Kind staff,  about to be a favorite for good.

By far the best bbq I have eaten in a while.  I had the pulled pork bbq sandwich.  The meat was tender and moist. A friend had the slider trio and was impressed with the brisket and turkey.  Loved the atmosphere (had a choice of dining inside or outside).  From the time you walked in the door to the time you left everyone was very friendly and accommodating.  I absolutely have nothing bad to say about Foggy Bottom BBQ.  Love, love, love!!
I came here for the Saint Patrick's Day special... Pastrami brisket!!!! And they did not disappoint.... If you're asking, is it worth the drive? It is.  I will be back

Best BBQ in Lawrenceville and have had in awhile!  Service is fantastic, America so nice, great with suggestions and service.  Wife enjoyed sampling the different BBQ meets on sliders, and I loved the brisket sandwich with pamento cheese.  Wonderful Brunswick Stew and mixed greens.  Looking forward to returning...
Bbq very good .
Very very tasty and not stingy with the food. Love it will be back very soon
I use to drive to the Loganville location which was a pain but totally worth it. This location is just as good. I am a frequent flyer here for sure. Beautiful restaurant and great food.
My wife and I really enjoyed our food,and the service is great.
Very good food
Food was great and service was amazing. Highly recommend the ribs!
Excellent, very pleasant service and sterile.
Good food and service. Very cold inside on a cold day.
Always hit the mark with good bbq!
Good bbq!
WOW...what more can i say.. amazing food and the most tender BBQ ever eaten. Will be going back.
Delicious! Follow the smoke its intoxicanting:)
The service was amazing and the sliders were great
Great bbq loved the sauces and Ali was extremely friendly and helpful! Loved the fried pickles!
Wonderful food, great service and awesome blues playing in the background! Who could ask for more? Highly recommend!...
Very good
Best place for BBQ!  We love our waitress!!

Simple environment with a variety of seating choices. Outside seating looks desirable when weather permits. Large menu with lots of menu selections with healthy portions. They have sides for days! My wife and I shared the pit boss bbq platter..3 choices of 5 selections of meat, 2 sides all accompanied with Texas toast. Our server was fantastic and was at times able to give us samples to secure our selections. We will definitely return again in warmer weather! Btw...food was delicious and very fairly priced.

OMG!!!!😃Today is the first time I've eaten from this restaurant but I can assure you it won't be My last!!!! My Hubby and I chose this place for Our anniversary dinner. We ordered the beef brisket platters and EVERYTHING was sooooo delicious!!!!😄 The food had such a homemade taste!!!!😃 I look forward to Our next purchase in the near future!!!!😁

Just horrible! My fiancé, me and our two two-year old girls came here to eat two weeks ago, on a Thursday.  I ordered the brisket sliders and my fiancé got a burger. We also ordered chicken tenders and mac&cheese for our girls! Let me start with mine. The brisket was soooo dry and the bread looked like it has been sitting outside for a while. My fiancé’s burger wasn’t the best either. He said that for a bbq place, it actually was bad.  Also I tasted the chicken tenders and the mac&cheese. The chicken looked like it was fryer in old oil and the mac&cheese was totally unseasoned. Like it had no flavor at all! Not even salt! Which makes me wonder how it was possible since the salt should already be in the cheese sauce...  Anyway, we tried this place because of all the nice reviews it had. But for us it was just horrible and we will never go again.
The food and service was excellent!
Very good.
Great service, location, average bbq, killer sides. Very consistent!
Ordered from here to go and the food was soooo good! I highly recommend the pork and the Mac and cheese! We will definitely be ordering from here again!

When the wife out eats you at a place like, you know its got to be a special place. Wear your up loose fitting clothes folks. You'll thank me later.  The ribs are meaty, the pulled pork is moist and tasty, and the sides are plentiful and delicious.
Beef brisket was tender and tasty. Mac and cheese is a great side

First they're in the middle of downtown Lawrenceville so parking there is minimal at best. I stopped by for a BBQ pork sandwich to go. Dried out pork like it had been sitting under a heat lamp.  Their other location in Loganville very good & we have been there numerous times. I will try the Lawrenceville location again just to see if I caught them at a bad time.
Food is awesome. The red beans and rice was delicious and so were the chicken sliders. If i could give 10 stars, I would.
I eat at this location for lunch sometimes. I always order the triple slider combo and it never disappoints. They give you plenty of meat on your sandwiches and have some good sides to go with it.
Outstanding!  Food was excellent and the service was the incredible southern charm that I know and love.  Will definitely be back!
I must say this is our new favorite bbq place.  Ribs were delicious.  Chicken was delicious.  Sides were delicious.   People were friendly and there was a diverse group of customers.  We will be back
Best orka ever!!!!!!!!!!!

The food was excellent!  The red beans and rice was delicious.  The collards were perfect and I loved the spice.  The beef , brisket and ribs was super tender and I just loved it.  The staff was amazing and the atmosphere was beautiful.  Thank you Stacy and Christi for such a great experience.  I will defiantly be coming back soon.

BAD!!! They took my donuts and my car didnt read directions right i thought it was a store, WHOOPS turns it its a bbq place they were confused when my son had a panic attack because hes scared of dead animals hes now traumitized becuase of you, anyways this place is cool my son is now autistic

caption: No seasoning of the food.
Bbq was great, potato salad was awsome. Good service. We really enjoyed it.
Really great food, nice place, super staff. We'll be back.
Dine in is available. Great food, had brisket and ribs all done perfectly. Staff was great and treated us well. Staff was wearing face masks.
Great BBQ!
Brisket tacos are awesome and the best potato salad ever!
Amazing brisket, people , and atmosphere. Best smoked flavor . Meat so tender that you can't even pick it up with a fork....falls apart , shredded and so so juicy.
Ribs, wings, brisket you name it it is delicious.  Had five sides all were outstanding.. so many GF options my wife loved that part!!
The food here was really good!  The staff was awesome as well!

The atmosphere was cool. You can sit outside. I got the pulled pork plate with Mac and cheese ,baked beans and a side of brunswick stew. The meat had good flavor even without sauce ,it was a little dry though. The Mac and cheese was good but you saw the separeted grease . The beans were ok. The stew was pretty good. My husband got the half rack of ribs. He said the flavor was good.

First time here and everything was great! Fried Cajun ribs was definitely different and excellent! Pit master plate our 3 meats chicken, brisket, turkey and all were great also. Mac n cheese, Brunswick stew and Collards were all delicious too. I ordered our food for pickup, I was greeted soon as I walked in at the door and the place was very clean and the ladies were very friendly. We will definitely be back and highly recommend for all to try!

This place had high ratings, and we found out quickly why. Great service, nice seating selection indoor and out, menu is very typical for a BBQ place, but the food sets itself apart. Highly recommend if you're in Gwinnett county!

This was our first time at Foggy Bottom BBQ in Lawrenceville and we had an amazing experience. The staff was very friendly and helpful. The food was amazing. My kids loved the ribs , and they have high standards when it comes to BBQ or any food. My girls ordered from the kids menu and it was just the right amount for them. Hands down the best BBQ in town. We will be repeat offenders.
The chicken and pulled pork sandwiches were great. Excellent red beans and rice. Try the banana pudding.
You HAVE to get the deep fried ribs
Great barbecue, Good prices, Excellent service. Highly recommended !
Amazing food. Our server was top notch. We will be back!!!

Service OK. Had the Brisket Plate with green beans and collards as a side, 16 dollars. Brisket was OK, but rather bland. Green beans were watered down in flavor and beyond tender. Collard greens had too much black pepper, giant stalks, and hardly any of the leaf. Not bad but not great either, in my opinion.
Awesome good, great environment, has a nice patio and customer service is upscale
Yummy
Good sides, good pulled pork (I like mine a little smokier) I know bbq is subjective along with most food. They started charging upcharge on couple sides but still good deal on bogo free Wednesday.
Good pulled pork sandwich, mac and cheese was ok (not bad, was just expecting better). Really good banana pudding

I had high hopes for this place but I was severely disappointed. I ordered the half chicken with baked beans and collard greens. My family had the brunswick stew, mac n cheese, potatoe salad & red beans n rice. Omg, the food was not good at all. The only thing we ate was the red beans n rice. The chicken was very dry and bland. The collard greens was bland and sitting in a cup full of unseasoned water. *vomits* If you want good seasoned , juicy bbq chicken and BBQ food (in general) go to Jimmy Nix!! Sorry but I will not go to this place again
Great food.
Delicious!

You ever go out to lunch and feel as if you could have gotten what you ate "anywhere else?" Not so with Foggy Bottom BBQ. From the ambiance of the restaurant, which included outdoor seating overlooking the downtown square in Lawrenceville, to plenty of indoor eating, this place offers some character.  And the food! Very solid BBQ! Pulled pork melts in your mouth. Give it a try next time you are hunting a place to eat. It's the difference in eating in a small local restaurant versus eating in a chain. That's the sum of it.  For us, we'll be back (maybe for dinner tonight)!
Great BBQ. Great service. Have to try the pork rinds.
Good service.  Good food.
Brisket sandwich topped with pimento cheese! Ummm.

This place is a hidden gem! I had the bbq chicken and brisket tacos with a side of Mac and cheese. It was freaking awesome and the service was just as great! My waitress Ali was super helpful with pointing out the best menu items (it was my first time eating here). The Mac and cheese is a must have! Definitely will be back !
Over priced, tiny portions, incredibly dry pulled pork. No soul at this "bbq" place what so ever.
We enjoyed the evening on the outdoor patio; great setting to enjoy downtown Lawrenceville.  Fries were quite good.
Friendly staff, great brisket and wonderful fried okra!
Very good pulled Pork, Brunswick stew is pretty good, Mac and red beans & rice are ok. Good service, great location. Look forward to trying more.I hear the pimento cheese is great.
Best service and Bar b que
Love love the fried pickle spears! The brisket is very tasty, the slaw is creamy, and the pimento cheese is on point. Don't forget the delicious banana pudding!
The pulled pork was delish and so were the sweet potato fries. Service was very good and the staff friendly.
It's really good food!!!
Awesome stew and the smoked wings are to die for!

FABULOUS! Staff was very friendly, food was great. I had one side item that was a wee bit spicey for my taste, I mentioned it, not complaining, just mentioned, they took that item off our check. Dining room was very clean. This was our 1st visit but I am sure we will visit again. Oh, we were celebrating my husband's birthday but he didn't want me to mention it so, not sure what they do, if anything for special occasions.  See you guys again soon!  😀

Foggy Bottom is the absolute best ribs and BBQ I have ever eaten in my life.  My family loves the pulled pork.  I love the baby back ribs.  There is so much clean meat on the ribs and the meat just falls off.  I don't know what other BBQ places do for getting their ribs cause Foggy Bottom gets the ribs with the most meat.  Pulled pork isnt loaded with a lot of fat.  It is rare to ever get anything but clean, delicious pulled pork.  The mac n cheese is pretty good.  I personally don't like the beans.  I've had better but you can't touch the ribs and pulled pork.  Brisket is pretty good too.  Never tried the chicken.  They have another location in Loganville.  This is a must try BBQ place.
Truly amazing bbq with wonderful service. I will absolutely be back.
I went with a friend recently and will certainly go back. It was the best barbecue sandwich I had in this area. Highly recommend!!
Food was good 👌👍 and the staff was nice will go back 👍 for sure 👍
Very beautiful 😍 food and very kind staff

The food was excellent and so was the service. You get a lot of food for the price. Being located so close to the town square enhanced the outdoor dining experience. I would definitely recommend this place.
This is a great BBQ place.
Food was awesome!!  Service was top notch!!
I tried a good variety of items. Some needed a bit more salt... Some a bit more heat...but hey, you can always add that easier than taking it away. I shall return. ( Also, really good service )

First time eating here. Wasn't impressed, I order a pulled  chicken sandwich. I ended up with  pulled pork. Had way to much liquid smoke.  It was very dry. It  was take out. Not sure I would try it again..

Pickup for family and couldn’t tell the difference in an adult chicken tender basket for $10.00 versus the kids tender for $5.00. Just want everyone to be informed in advance. Not worth paying for. Spoke with the Manager (think her name was Kim or Kelly) and she let me know that was correct and to maybe call them to order versus going on Google. What that had to do with the portion sizes I really don’t know. Last visit to Foggy Bottom.

Good space and service. Actual BBQ was lacking good seasoning, so bland. I'd hoped testing the homemade sauce options could make the taste of the meat better and add moisture, but each flavor made each bite worse, in different ways. No dessert highlights; banana pudding tasted and looked exactly how you'd expect.
Amazing BBQ! Some of the best brisket and chicken wings I've ever had.

The brisket was flavorful, juicy, and tender. Their sweet potato fries was a decadent blend of crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. The ribs were seasoned perfectly and slid right off the bone but slightly dry and hard at the ends. The food is a solid 4 stars. My only qualm was that the portions were a bit scanty. As for the service, WOW! Our server was so very polite and accommodating! I will definitely be visiting again.

We've gone 3 or 4 times now, and the BBQ is always solid. They do a great job with side dishes in particular, and I actually think the turkey is their best of the smoked meats.  For anyone not familiar with the area, parking can be a bit of a challenge.
Great place very modern rustic...
Great food and service!
Fantastic food, fun staff, quick service.
The experience and the food was amazing. Kelly took great care of us. The brisket wasn't great but everything else was. Would definitely go back
I had the pulled pork sandwich and Brunswick stew. Portion sizes are great. Service was friendly and fast. Will be returning for lunch often.
Delicious BBQ and great service
It was so good!!
The brisket plate is excellent! Very friendly staff
First time eating wasn't really impressed with it. Not a lot to choose from if your don't eat meat. Some of the food was cold too. Not a good experience.
The food was delicious and staff friendly and helpful
Banana pudding was fabulous.
Good food in DT Lawrenceville!
Very good meal. Large portions and full of flavour.
Good service a d good food
Super good food and pork skins
Is good place

The review posted three weeks ago supposedly by "Joong Yoo" is a FAKE review. Joong Yoo is the owner of the restaurant I work at in Buford and he has NEVER even been to Foggy Bottom Bbq. Furthermore, our previous employee, Kelly, your current manager, signed into our business email without authorization and wrote this false review which will be reported immediately!!!!!!!!!
Great BBQ! Brisket is where it's at.
Food was delicious and the service was friendly and pleasant.  Great family atmosphere.
Delicious food
Great BBQ. They even offer North Carolina style which reminds of my second home.

Pretty good bbq. I had the big plate the first time I went there had barbecue pork brisket and sausage I’ll route pretty good the sausage is amazing now they have a separate sausage dish a definite must try!

Great spot on the Lawrenceville square for Bar B Q. Their pork rinds are so good and made to order. When they bring them to the table they are just a crackling. I had the Bar B Q tacos which are awesome. You get three so I choose a different meat for each one. They are loaded with meat and I can only eat two of them.

First time visiting in Jan 2020 and I'll definitely be back. We started with some fresh pork rinds which are still crackling when they come out with a spicy dipping sauce that's out of this world. I got the brisket and pimento cheese sandwich and it was just right. We had a large party which they easily accommodated and the vibe was perfect for a family get together. Very kid friendly. The food portions are generous and we literally got our food 15 minutes after placing our order on a Friday night. They have this down to a science. Great spot in the heart of downtown Lawrenceville.
Good food and good portions for the price. I do agree with the other reviewers the brisket is dry and needs a bit more salt in the rub.
BY FAR BEST BBQ IN LOGANVILLE
Best bbq ever!!! Try the brisket or ribs!!! But theres nothing bad!
Great food. Awesome service! Even late at nite! Thx

So unhappy!!! Was maybe 3 people in restaurant I got a rack of ribs, quart of collards, and a quart of Mac and cheese. Collards were dry and have a fishy taste to them. Mac and cheese is the consistency of baby food. It is complete mush. Ribs were okay. I’m baffled never had an issue at the Loganville location. Thanks for wasting my $50🤬🤬 I do not recommend this place at all.
This is the only BBQ that I will enjoy, other than my own!
Prices seem a bit steep, food is good though
Very nice barbecue restaurant. Nice people, great menu selection and delicious food.
Delicious!! This place PROVES that not all barbeque is equal.. had the best side of beans and rice here, too! Nice casual atmosphere.. put a star on it!
Brisket is always good...I get it every time.
Excellent BBQ and sides. Staff is super friendly and service is always quick. A definite lunch stop if you're around the square in Lawrenceville!
It's kind of pricey for average BBQ

Very good restraunt, great staff, and a good atmosphere. I got the BBQ Pork Sandwhich which was a large amount to eat (for me) and basically had 0 fat. Best BBQ restraunt around. Thanks! I definitely recommend visiting.

My customer experience was awesome on Thanksgiving Eve. The service and food was outstanding especially smoke Turkey. In my opinion Foogy bottom is the best kept secret in Lawrenceville. Happy holidays  Don't take my word drop in and check it out
Enjoyed the ribs.
Great service. Quick polite and efficient. Food taste wonderful! Love this place.
Real Good BBQ Had a pulled pork special tonite Buy one get one free. Great service too.
Decent bbq with great service
I had the brisket sandwich. It was huge. I loved it! Can't stop talking about it. Great family place to eat.
Food was excellent and the service was OUTSTANDING

Had the baby back ribs. They were undercooked to the point that meat in some parts were white. The appetizer and sides both were very bland. I gave them 1 star for the coca cola it came with ice and it was cold.
Lunch was great!
The food was very good and the staff was friendly and efficient. I'd recommend trying it if you haven't.
Too expensive Food is ok Make sure you clarify what you want to order Try to condense your bill, if so. Got some fried ribs, not a fan!!
Ribs and brisket were awesome
Best place that I have ever eaten at

Fried pickles were crunchy and the sauce was nice and tangy.  The brisket was perfectly cooked,  a little lacking on flavor but their Original Sauce more than made up for it. The collards were perfectly seasoned and had a little kick to them. The potato salad had the perfect combination of flavor and texture. The sweet tea was on point. The service was excellent.
Great food! I had there red beans and rice, can't suggest it enough.
I love the brisket slides. Good service
Enough for 2 of us to share.
The wings are fabulous!
Great lunch for a meeting with a colleague
Alright food
Love this place. Best friend okra in town!
I had ribs there today (Monday) and they tasted old, hard and was not worth my $$. The mac & cheese was fake. I will not retun.
The best BBQ, every. Brunswick stew the best,!
Awesome bbq and great service! Brisket sandwich was awesome!
Great food and great service !

First time customer. Loved the brisket.  I didnt care for the potato salad (I'm a mustard and sweet pickles potato salad person) my daughter loved the pork skins but, mac and cheese was dry and unappealing. French fries were good. The Brunswick stew was packed with meat and was really good. Service was great. Kinda pricey.
Awesome service and great tasting food.

The restaurant was clean and we received good service.  They had a small selection of draft beer and they served my craft beer in a plastic cup. The food was good or average for your typical BBQ.  The fried pickle spears for an app were a highlight to the visit.  The smoked sausage was the most shockingly good of the meats.  I tried a sample of all six choices of meats they offer. Nothing was bad.  And the food was served fresh.  But there was nothing other than the pickle spears and sausage that set this place apart from other BBQ joints.
The wings are always the best and are consistent. Cannot go wrong with the brisket. Fries and greens are the top sides.
Great food, friendly staff, and quick service. Always a win.
So glad to see this location open in Lawrenceville! Food was great, as always, and we had great service from Izzy. I'll be back!
Pretty good BBQ. A lot of different sauce varieties. I would visit here again.

Love this place. Went to the original in Loganville and then saw this new location in Lawrenceville. My wife loves the Brisket Tacos. I like the Smoked Chicken and Turkey as well. Brunswick Stew and Baked Beans are also good as well. Service at both is excellent. Either location is a win.
Two words ! Fried Ribs! Omg they are delicious!!! And the portion size is huge ..
Sub par BBQ, gets 2 stars because service was good
Really tender and delicious brisket. Had a good smokey flavor to it. Potato salad was also very good. The staff is friendly and inviting. Will definitely be back whenever we are in town.

It comes well laid out.  The fries were warm and tasty.  The pork was very bland.  The only flavorful pieces I found had the rub distilled on them. Stew wasn't the best. I found it weird that the toast was only toasted on 1 side. It was crunchy on that side.  But again, tasteless. Nice place though.
Great food!!!
Very good authentic food, mac&cheese really delicious. Will be going back

Hit and miss.  More of a hit - the meats are good.  Why can't they serve salad as a side?  If they had low carb sides I would go there more.  Thinking of the sides I have had: The fries and sweet potato fries are good --but why does the kitchen send them to you covered in grease?  Yuck.  And the banana pudding is made by someone who doesn't care or has never had good banana pudding.  It's no secret...follow the recipe on the side of the vanilla wafers box.  The red rice and beans or the Brunswick stew...mehhh.
Amazing BBQ!!
Never disappoints....always good. Everything!

Best smoked wings I've ever had.  Good local brews.  The rice and beans was top notch.  Vinegar based slaw... thank you.  The spicy sauce could be spicier.  But also amazing fried pickles.  Good job guys.

Had the brisket, Brunswick stew, and pork skins.  Brisket was tender and very well seasoned, didn't really need bbq sauce.  Brunswick stew was meaty and flavorful.  The pork skins were made to order, very crunchy.  Only four stars just because the brisket was warm, not hot.
Good local BBQ. The brisket is the star on the menu, but the fresh pork rinds, pork, and sides are all good
Very good food. Took a little to much time to get it out to us.

The brisket was tender and absolutely to die for! The pimento cheese tasty combined & the collards and macaroni & cheese were true southern recipes! This born & bred GA boy is truly impressed! Well-worth a try!
Great ribs! Also check out the new sides fried okra and cream corn. The Mac and cheese with spicy BBQ sauce is a go to.
Service was good and food proportions was phenomenal for the price.

GREAT BBQ!!! THE FRIED RIBS???? OMG YOU HAVE TO TRY. THE MAC AND CHEESE, SO GOOD!!! BBQ IS BETTER THEN ALOT OF BBQ RESTAURANTS I ATE AT BEFORE. HANDS DOWN ONE OF THE BEST!!! I HAVE A NEW BBQ RESTAURANT!!!! LOVE IT!! WAITRESS WAS VERY NICE .
Great food & great service as always! Gail was a GREAT waitress & we will ask for her next time..
Good service.

Great place. 530 on a Saturday evening, got seated immediately (though it got busier as we ate). Attentive waitress brought delicious pulled pork, beans, and brunswick stew. Good Carolina and vinegar sauces. Can't wait to go back!
Amazing sauce, great meats, and wonderful sides. The potato salad is a religious experience!
It w as good
Tried the sample platter. Can’t believe I finished it. Ribs were dry. Everything else was perfect.
If you wamt great service and amazing bbq and haven't been to Foggy Bottom yet then you're doing it wrong!!
Always terrific! Aleigh was our waitress and gave great service.  We've never been dissatisfied here!
Great food and great service!
Excellent brisket. Good service.
Came hungry left full. Sauce is ok. Prices are fair
Been here several times now. Everything is really good. I just wish they had green beans on the permanent menu.
Great service and good food
Absolutely delicious. As for BBQ, definitely worth the the visit. The fried ribs are a must try!
Brisket was "melt in your mouth" Good !

Upon sitting here, atleast 6 other people have come here and have received and eaten their food. When we walked in it took 5 minutes to even get served or greeted. When I  asked the server why this was she had an attitude. But hey that's her tip. This location be will  my NOT be receiving my service again.

It has a nice, clean, laid back atmosphere. The hostess and servers were welcoming and sweet. The food is good as well. It wasnt the best bbq I've ever had in my life, but it was very good. Better than I can make! Will def go back
Fresh popping pork rinds are amazing
Absolutely great BBQ!
The barbeque is very good!
Good service, good food, nice atmosphere

We have been here several times and we love this place! All the food is delicious and the staff is awesome.  We are fast becoming regulars and we're bringing friends with us, as well as spreading the word to others about the best BBQ in   Lawrenceville.

Foggy Bottom is becoming one of our regular favorites! The freshly made pork skins are the main reason. They are amazing and it's so rare to find a genuine keto appetizer. The service is always friendly, the prices aren't too bad, and Downtown Lawrenceville is the place to be.
The ribs and okra were Amazing!

I ordered from there and both of the employees was very nice one black and one white they were very pleasant and I ordered the brisket and Wing's and they give you a nice size amount of meat and I will go back there.
Love the peppery brisket with added spicy bbq sauce on top.
Yum!
All Great!
That brisket is the bomb dot com. Yes yes.
Food was very good, but the portions were small.
Cajun fried ribs..the bomb diggity!
Great service great Bar b que  I look forward to. Visiting again

Went here for the second time. The lack of actual silverware and plates is bothersome and feels cheap. The meats are okay, nothing special,  no big flavors. The star here is the potato salad.  I know we should keep it local, but if a local meal costs twice of the chain and not even half of the flavor, it doesn't make sense to keep it local

Love this place. Enjoyed our food and server was great. I left my credit card and they had it when I called, which I was appreciative of their honesty. A definite must try of you're looking for a great place on the Sqaure in Lawrenceville.
Grat pulled pork. Not really greasy as other local BBQ restaurants are.
Smoked chicken sa n switch & Brunswick Stew was the Best!! 😊
Delicious food. Service was good. If I was in the area I would certainly go here again. The brisket sandwich was tender and large, I couldn't finish it.
Good stuff. I suggest the friend pickles for sure.
Great customer, service great food. Accomadated our large family
Good service. Good food.

Best beef brisket I've ever had; definitely try their original sauce. The sides (fried okra and potato salad) were also delicious. Nice selection of beers on tap. Service was prompt and friendly. All-in-all, I highly recommend Foggy Bottom if you're looking for barbecue in Lawrenceville.

Great spot for BBQ. The pulled pork is arguably the best I’ve had in a long time. The brisket is a bit dry and too lean and thin sliced  to hold in any juices. The Ribs were good but lacked any bark. The pulled pork alone is enough to warrant a visit! I’ll definitely be back for that. Their sauces are pretty good. The original is the best. The spicy sauce tastes like its spice comes from black pepper instead of a red pepper sauce. The vinegar sauce tastes like straight vinegar without any seasoning. The red beans and rice were great and seasoned well with just the right kick. This place is a must try if you are a BBQ lover.
Great Experience! Food was great. Staff was very nice.

The brisket, amazing. The pulled pork, to die for. The ribs, fall off the bone delicious. You know you're at a good bbq place when the meat is seasoned so well that you don't even need the extra sauces. But even then, the sauces were fantastic! Highly recommend🎉
Great food and atmosphere
The brisket and sweet potato fries were amazing! The service was great and attentive.
very good and good portions! their Red beans and rice awesome!!!
Heck yeah! This place is delicious. Friendly management and the owner walks around!

Friendly staff. Pork skins appetizer are fresh made and come to the table crackling! Pulled pork was tender and yummy with the Carolina Sweet sauce.  Mac and cheese was so good. Baked beans have an interesting fruity flavor.  Tea is sweet and 0erfrct with BBQ.
My first time coming here and I waited so long for the foods i order. Slow service. I don't under stand it I will just go somewhere else next time downtown for bbq

The best smoked chicken wings in Gwinnett County!  Excellent customer service:  friendly, fast & efficient!  No longer need to go all the way to Fox Bros. for a good smoked wing!  Great job, Foggy Bottom!  Keep up the good work!

Once again after reading the multiple positive reviews about this restaurant we had to try it.... We are barbecue addicts and will follow rumors of outstanding briskets and ribs for hundreds of .miles... Last night we ventured into Foggy Bottoms wanting a plate of ribs and a salad only to be told the ribs had sold out, no salad and a few other items qere also 86'd I ended up with the house brisket pimiento cheese sandwich  ... which was decent. My wife ended up with chicken wings which were small. .  . The potato salad, the cole slaw need a hell of alot of work and a lot less mayonnaise  .. But the thing that sealed the deal with us and .ade this joint a two star was the banana pudding.. This was without a doubt the worse banana pudding we've purchased in any restaurant anywhere... We left feeling totally let down..

Not the worst BBQ I've ever had, but close. Fried okra was good, but that's the only thing that wasn't terrible. Brisket was tender and juicy, but had absolutely no flavor. Half of my pulled pork wasn't even "pulled", it was just a big chunk of meat. Collards were bland and not very good. The Glory brand canned collards from the grocery store are significantly better than the collards here. To top it all off, all four of the BBQ sauces here are terrible. I had a suspicion the food would be subpar after seeing the prices, combined with the plastic silverware and the plastic cup they brought out for the beer my girlfriend ordered. Staff was friendly and service was decent, but I wouldn't eat here again even if the food was free.
